  "prompt": "How do I link multiple Drive accounts?",
  "response": "Here are a few ways to link or manage multiple Google Drive accounts:\n\n1. Browser Method:\n- Open Chrome\n- Click on your profile picture\n- Select \"Add another account\"\n- Sign in with your additional Google account\n- Switch between accounts using the profile menu\n\n2. Mobile App Method:\n- Open Google Drive app\n- Tap your profile picture\n- Select \"Add another account\"\n- Sign in with additional account\n- Switch between accounts by tapping profile picture\n\n3. Desktop Method:\n- Open Drive for desktop\n- Click account menu\n- Select \"Add account\"\n- Sign in with additional account\n\n4. Alternative Third-Party Tools:\n- Backup & Sync from Google\n- Odrive\n- MultCloud\n- CloudMounter\n\nTips:\n- Use different browsers for simultaneous access\n- Consider using Google Workspace for unified management\n- Check each method's specific steps for your device/version\n\nRecommendation: Choose the method most convenient for your workflow and device type.",
